cutter.tools

Class UnitTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • cutter.tools.UnitTest

  • public class UnitTest
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements unit tests for java methods. Its possible to test multiple types within the same UnitTest
    Author:
    Phil Niehus Copyright (C) 2015 Phil Niehus

      • evaluateMultiple

        public void evaluateMultiple(java.util.ArrayList actual,
                             java.util.ArrayList expected)
        This method can be used to evaluate multiple results. All objects contained in the ArrayList should however
        be instances of the same class.
        This method supports all basic types that are available in java.
        Parameters:
        actual - An ArrayList of all actual values
        expected - An ArrayList of expected values
